12-13 February - Lemon Shiffon Pie (Chiffon)

- 1   pie crust (baked)
- 1   teaspoon unflavored gelatin
- 1/4 cup cold water
- 3   large eggs, separated
- 1   cup sugar
- 1/2 cup lemon juice
- 2   teaspoon lemon zest
- 2-3 drops yellow food coloring
- 1   cup La Creme whipped topping, thawed (Cool Whip)
- chocolate shavings
- lemon slices

Soak gelatin in water. In a double boiler over gently simmering water, beat egg yolks, ad 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice. Cook, stirring until mixture coats the back of a spoon. Add grated lemon peel, gelatin, and food coloring. Stir well. Cool in refrigerator 1/2 hour until slightly thickened. 

Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar, fold into lemon mixture. Fold in La Creme. 

Spoon into baked pie shell. Refrigerate 2-3 hours before serving. Garnish with chocolate shavings and lemon slices. Serves 8.